{
  "text": "Out of all pituitary tumors, 3-15% are considered atypical pituitary adenomas, and only 0.1-0.2% are frank pituitary carcinomas defined by the presence of craniospinal and/or systemic metastasis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Due to the paucity of cases, our current understanding of this unique subpopulation of pituitary neoplasms is very limited. Thus, the accumulation of relevant reports is critical for expanding our knowledge on this rare disease.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "207075830",
    "[CITATION_2]": "39682097"
